{
  "command": "entity stores",
  "description": "Get IaaS storage info behind entity data (metric/log/trace/event stores)\n\nDiscover the IaaS layer storage locations (SLS project, logstore, metricstore)\nbacking an entity type's metric_set, log_set, trace_set, or event_set.\n\nUse this when you need to:\n- Inspect/debug raw storage metadata behind an entity\n- Manually find SLS project/metricstore or project/logstore for a raw fallback\n- Understand what data stores exist for an entity type\n\nThis is the startup view for an entity's data access layer. Use it after\nentity search when you need to understand which datasets exist for the\nconcrete entity and which physical storage each dataset uses.\n\nThe result is grouped by storage_info. Each storage group lists the datasets\nbacked by that storage and the requested entities. This lets agents see when\nmultiple data_sets share the same storage without running separate\numodel datasets and entity stores calls.\n\nPass entity_ids. Different entities of the same type\noften live in different stores (different clusters, projects, regions),\nso the storage answer is per-entity, not per-type. Get entity IDs from\nentity search first.\n\nAlways forward the user's time-range with --time-range so the backend returns\nthe storage bindings that were active during that period.\n\nRelated tools: log_set query and metric_set query (normal entity-bound path),\nmetric_store query and log_store query (raw fallback, also accept entity hints).\n",
